parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Throttle Lag in 2nd Gear at 5500 RPM
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The throttle lag can cause the motorcycle to hesitate or fail to accelerate, leading to potential accidents or near-misses, especially in heavy traffic conditions.
symptoms: The motorcycle fails to accelerate or hesitates when the throttle is opened in 2nd gear at 5500 RPM
resulting in a delay of 3-4 seconds before the bike responds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake valve can cause the valve to break off into the cylinder, leading to engine damage and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: abnormal ticking or noise from the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The throttle lag can cause the vehicle to hesitate or stall, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when merging or passing other vehicles.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or stalls when accelerating in second gear at 5500 RPM
the vehicle takes a few seconds to respond to throttle input
the vehicle accelerates slowly or erratically.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power and potentially lead to accidents or near-misses, especially when slowing down or coming to a stop.
symptoms: The engine stalls when slowing down or coming to a stop
the engine dies when blipping or revving the engine in neutral or gear
the engine takes several attempts to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty ECU Causing Stalling and Lag
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty ECU can cause the motorcycle to stall when coasting or stopping, and lag when accelerating at certain RPM ranges, creating a dangerous situation for the rider and other motor vehicles in the vicinity.
symptoms: The motorcycle stalls when coasting or stopping
lags when accelerating at certain RPM ranges (around 5500 RPM in 2nd gear)
has a severe "lag" when riding at 5500 RPM's in 2nd gear
and has a loss of power when attempting to merge on the highway.
